<div id="pf21" class="pf wa hd" data-page-no="21"><div class="pc pc21 wa hd"><img class="bi x0 y0 wb he" alt="" src="bg21.png"/><div class="t m2de x2f h19 y509 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON 4 July 20-26 </div><div class="t m45e xc3 h2a y39e ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MC2 52Ennufl </div><div class="t m45f xbb h2e y50a ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">riEgin </div><div class="t m460 x87 h2f y50a ff3 fs17 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">[LIS </div><div class="t m461 x1f h30 y50b ff1 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">III </div><div class="t m362 x38 h19 y50c ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;For I know that my Redeemer lives, </div><div class="t m462 x53 h19 y447 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and at last he will stand upon the </div><div class="t mef x48 h19 y50d ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">earth; </div><div class="t m463 x38 h19 y449 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and after my skin has been thus </div><div class="t m361 x48 h19 y9f ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">destroyed, </div><div class="t m464 x53 h19 y50e ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">then from my flesh I shall see </div><div class="t m465 x48 h19 y50f ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God, </div><div class="t m466 x38 h19 y6f ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">whom I shall see on my side, </div><div class="t m95 x53 h19 y44d ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and my eyes shall behold, and not </div><div class="t m467 x55 h19 y44e ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">another&quot; (Job 19:25-27, RSV). </div><div class="t m399 x38 h17 y450 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This lesson covers Job 12 through </div><div class="t m468 x1 h17 y451 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">20. It seems proper to skip lightly over </div><div class="t m469 x1f h17 y510 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">these chapters, because so much that </div><div class="t m27a x1f h17 y453 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">is said by the three friends is repetition </div><div class="t m46a x1f h17 y511 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of what th6y have already said in the </div><div class="t m3c5 x1f h17 y454 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">first dialogue. Someone has compared </div><div class="t m46b x1f h17 y512 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the speeches of Job&apos;s friends to a </div><div class="t m46c x1f h17 y513 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">series of wheels rotating on the same </div><div class="t m46d x1f h17 y3a ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">axle. There is little progress, only </div><div class="t m46e x1f h17 y514 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">restatement of the erroneous </div><div class="t m46f x1f h17 y515 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">traditions of their time. </div><div class="t m470 x45 h17 y457 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s speeches are different. &quot;From </div><div class="t m261 x1f h17 y516 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the depths of discouragement and </div><div class="t m381 x1f h17 y459 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">despondency Job rose to the heights </div><div class="t m471 x1f h17 y45a ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of implicit trust in the mercy and the </div><div class="t m472 x1f h17 y517 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">saving power of </div><div class="t m386 x26 h17 y45b ff6 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God.&quot;—Prophets and </div><div class="t m393 x1f h17 y518 ff6 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Kings, </div><div class="t m3a6 x3 h17 y45c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. 163. This spiritual progress </div><div class="t m2a5 x1f h17 y45d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">was slow and painful, but it can be </div><div class="t m39e x4c h17 y45e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">seen in the successive speeches of </div><div class="t m473 x4c h17 y45f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job. This lesson will pick up some of </div><div class="t m474 x4c h17 y460 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">these evidences of dawn in the dark </div><div class="t m475 x4c h17 y519 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">night of Job&apos;s sorrow. </div><div class="t m476 x45 h17 y462 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It must be borne in mind that Job did </div><div class="t m477 x4c h17 y51a ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">not have the slightest inkling of the </div><div class="t m478 x4c h17 y463 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reasons for his suffering. He knew </div><div class="t m479 x4c h17 y464 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">nothing of the dialogue between the </div><div class="t m47a x4c h17 y89 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lord and Satan. He did not know that </div><div class="t m47b x4c h17 y465 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">he was a test case before the universe </div><div class="t m47c x4c h17 y466 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as to whether anyone really served </div><div class="t m47d x22 h17 y51b ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God out of pure loyalty and faith. </div><div class="t m47b x49 h17 y51c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It also must be remembered that Job </div><div class="t m47e x22 h17 y469 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">must not be judged on the basis of his  </div><div class="t m47f x93 h17 y50c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">early discouragement or of his </div><div class="t m480 x93 h17 y51d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">repeated accusations against God. </div><div class="t m481 x93 h17 y51e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Lord evaluated Job during those </div><div class="t m482 x93 h17 y51f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">trying months of anguish, not on the </div><div class="t m483 x30 h17 y9f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">basis of his questions and complaints, </div><div class="t m484 x30 h17 y520 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">but on the basis of what he would be </div><div class="t m485 x93 h17 y50f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">when he ultimately emerged from his </div><div class="t m486 x93 h17 y521 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">dark night. God sees His people, not </div><div class="t m487 x93 h17 y522 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as they are, but as they will be. He is </div><div class="t m488 x30 h17 y523 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">like the parent who sees in the </div><div class="t m489 x30 h17 y256 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">immature child the eventual mature </div><div class="t m48a x30 h17 y524 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">man or woman—only God&apos;s </div><div class="t m328 x30 h17 ya7 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">foreknowledge is accurate and </div><div class="t m3a5 x30 h17 y525 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">complete. </div><div class="t m48b x28 h17 y526 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The </div><div class="t m37b xd h17 y527 ff6 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">S.D.A. Bible Commentary </div><div class="t m48c x30 h17 y528 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">organizes the second dialogue, or </div><div class="t m48d x30 h17 y25b ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">cycle, as follows (see vol. 3, p. 496): </div><div class="t m48e x28 h17 y512 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m48f x9d h17 y529 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s first speech: he maintains </div><div class="t m490 x9d h17 y39 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his integrity, 12:1 to 14:22. </div><div class="t m491 x28 h17 yae ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m492 x71 h17 y52a ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eliphaz&apos;s speech: he reproves </div><div class="t m493 x9d h17 yb0 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job for impiety, 15:1-35. </div><div class="t m494 x28 h17 yb2 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m10f x9d h17 yb3 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s second speech:, he accuses </div><div class="t m25d x9d h17 yb4 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his friends of being unmerciful, </div><div class="t m495 x71 h17 y516 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">16:1 to 17:16. </div><div class="t m496 x28 h17 y52b ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m497 x9d h17 y52c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bildad&apos;s speech: he insists that </div><div class="t m3ac x9d h17 yb5 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">calamity overtakes the wicked, </div><div class="t m498 x71 h17 y517 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">18:1-21. </div><div class="t m44f x28 h17 y52d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m499 x9d h17 y52e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s third speech: he expresses </div><div class="t m49a x9d h17 y52f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his belief in the resurrection, </div><div class="t m498 x71 h17 y530 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">19:1-29. </div><div class="t m46c x28 h17 y531 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m49b x9d h17 y531 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Zophar&apos;s speech: he describes </div><div class="t m49c x9d h17 y266 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the present and future </div><div class="t m49d x9d h17 y532 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">punishment of the wicked, </div><div class="t mf5 x9d h17 y533 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">20:1-29. </div><div class="t m294 x30 h19 y534 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">DAILY HIGHLIGHTS </div><div class="t m63 x30 h19 yc1 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m2a0 x59 h19 y535 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Sovereignty of God </div><div class="t m36c xb0 h19 y536 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 12:12-14, 17-21) </div><div class="t m65 x30 h19 y465 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m387 x59 h19 y537 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Problem of Death </div><div class="t m151 xb0 h19 y538 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 14:10-13) </div><div class="t m67 x30 h19 y467 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t ma6 x59 h19 y539 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Trust in Tradition </div><div class="t m98 xb0 h19 y53a ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 15:7-10) </div><div class="t m69 x30 h19 y53b ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m365 x59 h19 y32a ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Words Versus Warmth </div><div class="t m298 xb0 h19 y53c ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 16:1-6) </div><div class="t m6b x30 h19 y53d ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m1c7 x59 h19 y53d ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">An Intercessor </div><div class="t m171 xb0 h19 yd1 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 16:19; 19:25) </div><div class="t m6d x30 h19 y53e ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m310 x59 h19 y53e ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A Cry of Anguish </div><div class="t mc8 xb0 h19 y53f ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 19:13-22) </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
